<dl id="n09128m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09128m">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09128m"> 128(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ancient of Days / hair of head pure wool</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">ANGEL: Daniel has left us a vivid picture: &ldquo;I beheld till thrones were placed, and the <mark>Ancient of the Days</mark> sat: His garment was white as snow, and the <mark>hair of His head like clean wool</mark> <small> <a name="TCE1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TCE1"><cite title="source">Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) I, 476b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
